propAutoComplete:
If `true`, the portion of the selected suggestion that has not been typed by the user,
known as the completion string, appears inline after the input cursor in the textbox.
The inline completion string is visually highlighted and has a selected state.
propAutoHighlight: If `true`, the first option is automatically highlighted.
propAutoSelect:
If `true`, the selected option becomes the value of the input
when the Autocomplete loses focus unless the user chooses
a different option or changes the character string in the input.
propBlurOnSelect:
Control if the input should be blurred when an option is selected:

- `false` the input is not blurred.
- `true` the input is always blurred.
- `touch` the input is blurred after a touch event.
- `mouse` the input is blurred after a mouse event.
propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propClearOnBlur:
If `true`, the input's text is cleared on blur if no value is selected.

Set to `true` if you want to help the user enter a new value.
Set to `false` if you want to help the user resume his search.
propClearOnEscape: If `true`, clear all values when the user presses escape and the popup is closed.
propClearText:
Override the default text for the *clear* icon button.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propCloseIcon: The icon to display in place of the default close icon.
propCloseText:
Override the default text for the *close popup* icon button.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propDebug:
If `true`, the popup will ignore the blur event if the input is filled.
You can inspect the popup markup with your browser tools.
Consider this option when you need to customize the component.
propDefaultValue: The default input value. Use when the component is not controlled.
propDisableClearable: If `true`, the input can't be cleared.
propDisableCloseOnSelect: If `true`, the popup won't close when a value is selected.
propDisabledItemsFocusable: If `true`, will allow focus on disabled items.
propDisableListWrap: If `true`, the list box in the popup will not wrap focus.
propDisablePortal: The `Popper` content will be inside the DOM hierarchy of the parent component.
propFilterOptions: A filter function that determines the options that are eligible.
propFilterSelectedOptions: If `true`, hide the selected options from the list box.
propForcePopupIcon: Force the visibility display of the popup icon.
propFreeSolo: If `true`, the Autocomplete is free solo, meaning that the user input is not bound to provided options.
propFullWidth: If `true`, the input will take up the full width of its container.
propGetLimitTagsText: The label to display when the tags are truncated (`limitTags`).
propGetOptionDisabled: Used to determine the disabled state for a given option.
propGetOptionLabel:
Used to determine the string value for a given option.
It's used to fill the input (and the list box options if `renderOption` is not provided).
propGetOptionSelected:
Used to determine if an option is selected, considering the current value.
Uses strict equality by default.
propGroupBy:
If provided, the options will be grouped under the returned string.
The groupBy value is also used as the text for group headings when `renderGroup` is not provided.
propHandleHomeEndKeys:
If `true`, the component handles the "Home" and "End" keys when the popup is open.
It should move focus to the first option and last option, respectively.
propId:
This prop is used to help implement the accessibility logic.
If you don't provide this prop. It falls back to a randomly generated id.
propIncludeInputInList: If `true`, the highlight can move to the input.
propLimitTags:
The maximum number of tags that will be visible when not focused.
Set `-1` to disable the limit.
propListboxComponent: The component used to render the listbox.
propListboxProps: Props applied to the Listbox element.
propLoading: If `true`, the component is in a loading state.
propLoadingText:
Text to display when in a loading state.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propMultiple: If `true`, `value` must be an array and the menu will support multiple selections.
propNoOptionsText:
Text to display when there are no options.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propOnChange: Callback fired when the value changes.
propOnClose:
Callback fired when the popup requests to be closed.
Use in controlled mode (see open).
propOnHighlightChange: Callback fired when the highlight option changes.
propOnInputChange: Callback fired when the input value changes.
propOnOpen:
Callback fired when the popup requests to be opened.
Use in controlled mode (see open).
propOpenOnFocus: If `true`, the popup will open on input focus.
propOpenText:
Override the default text for the *open popup* icon button.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propPaperComponent: The component used to render the body of the popup.
propPopperComponent: The component used to position the popup.
propPopupIcon: The icon to display in place of the default popup icon.
propRenderOption: Render the option, use `getOptionLabel` by default.
propSelectOnFocus:
If `true`, the input's text is selected on focus.
It helps the user clear the selected value.
propValue:
The value of the autocomplete.

The value must have reference equality with the option in order to be selected.
You can customize the equality behavior with the `getOptionSelected` prop.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
styles: Avoid double tap issue on iOS
stylesFullWidth: Styles applied to the root element if `fullWidth={true}`.
stylesFocused: Pseudo-class applied to the root element if focused.
stylesTag: Styles applied to the tag elements, e.g. the chips.
stylesTagSizeSmall: Styles applied to the tag elements, e.g. the chips if `size="small"`.
stylesHasPopupIcon: Styles applied when the popup icon is rendered.
stylesHasClearIcon: Styles applied when the clear icon is rendered.
stylesInputRoot: Styles applied to the Input element.
stylesInput: Styles applied to the input element.
stylesInputFocused: Styles applied to the input element if tag focused.
stylesEndAdornment: Styles applied to the endAdornment element.
stylesClearIndicator: Styles applied to the clear indicator.
stylesPopupIndicator: Styles applied to the popup indicator.
stylesPopupIndicatorOpen: Styles applied to the popup indicator if the popup is open.
stylesPopper: Styles applied to the popper element.
stylesPopperDisablePortal: Styles applied to the popper element if `disablePortal={true}`.
stylesLoading: Styles applied to the loading wrapper.
stylesNoOptions: Styles applied to the no option wrapper.
stylesOption: Styles applied to the option elements.
stylesGroupLabel: Styles applied to the group's label elements.
stylesGroupUl: Styles applied to the group's ul elements.
